-- Canadian Cattle Herd Shrinks to Lowest Since 1994; Hogs Increase
-- B y   E l i z a b e t h   C a m p b e l l
-- 2012-08-21T13:41:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-21/canadian-cattle-herd-shrinks-to-lowest-since-1994-hogs-increase.html
The Canadian  cattle  herd as of July
1 fell 0.1 percent from a year earlier to the smallest since
1994,  Statistics Canada  said.  Producers held 13.52 million cattle as of July 1, down from
13.53 million a year earlier, the government agency said today
in a  report . The country had 12.87 million head of  hogs , up 1.5
percent from 12.685 million.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elizabeth Campbell in Chicago at 
 ecampbell14@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Steve Stroth at 
 sstroth@bloomberg.net . 